    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith enabled LSP color visualization, when file/buffer contains too many hex color strings, there are many `E849: Too many highlight and syntax groups` errors.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Have `lua-language-server` in `$PATH`.\n2. Create `~/.config/nvim-repro/init.lua` file with the following content:\n\n    ```lua\n    vim.lsp.document_color.enable(true)\n\n    _G.start_luals = function()\n      local config = { name = 'lua-ls', cmd = { 'lua-language-server' }, root_dir = vim.fn.getcwd() }\n      _G.client_id = vim.lsp.start(config)\n    end\n\n    _G.show_many_colors = function()\n      local lines = {}\n      for i = 1, 20000 do\n        lines[i] = string.format('local color_%06x = \"#%06x\"', i, i)\n      end\n      vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, lines)\n    end\n    ```\n\n3. `NVIM_APPNAME=nvim-repro nvim -- many-colors.lua`.\n4. `:write` to create an actual file on disk.\n5. `:lua start_luals()` and wait for a couple of seconds.\n6. `:lua show_many_colors()`. After couple of seconds it shows `E849: Too many highlight and syntax groups` error followed by many more after pressing `<Enter>`. This happens because maximum number of highlight groups possible is 19999.\n\nThe real life file that contains more than 19999 hex colors: https://github.com/meodai/color-names/blob/HEAD/src/colornames.csv .No error with `lua-language-server` as it is not a Lua file, but there can be an LSP server for csv or all files.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither (from best to worst):\n- No upper limit on highlight groups number.\n- Creating (much) more than 19999 highlight groups is possible. Maybe 100K?\n- No error when creating highlight groups beyond the limit.\n- No error coming from `vim.lsp.document_color` when creating many highlight groups.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-133+g6d43869aa0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes and no: has upper limit on highlight group number but doesn't have `vim.lsp.document_color` functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.19.11-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
