        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> can the `document_color` logic avoid creating too many highlights, or maybe constrain to viewport?\n\nEach new hex color requires a new highlight group. If there are >19999 hex colors to show, there will be >19999 highlight groups.\n\nConstraining to a viewport (I'd imagine) can only reasonably be done on per line basis. It is still possible for couple of lines to contain >19999 hex colors to highlight.\n\nI've tried using `pcall(api.nvim_set_hl, ...)`, but it looks like an error is still shown. If lifting or increasing the limit is not an option, then at least making this `pcall()` work by silently ignoring hex colors beyond the threshold should be possible.\n\nA more direct solution of always checking `vim.tbl_count(vim.api.nvim_get_hl(0, {})) < 19999` before creating a highlight group is possible, of course, but I don't think performance penalty is worth it.",
